ata-href=3D"https://nextplayso.substack.com/i/157245945/what-do-you-see-as-=
the-biggest-myths-people-get-wrong-about-job-negotiation"><svg xmlns=3D"htt=
p://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width=3D"18" height=3D"18" viewBox=3D"0 0 24 24" f=
ill=3D"none" stroke=3D"currentColor" stroke-width=3D"2" stroke-linecap=3D"r=
ound" stroke-linejoin=3D"round" class=3D"lucide lucide-link"><path d=3D"M10=
 13a5 5 0 0 0 7.54.54l3-3a5 5 0 0 0-7.07-7.07l-1.72 1.71"></path><path d=3D=
"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg=
></button></div></div></h3><p>The biggest myth is that if you negotiate the=
y might rescind your job offer. It just doesn=E2=80=99t happen, especially =
if you use collaborative but aggressive tactics. They just have too much in=
vested to let the right candidate go for something as silly as =E2=80=9Cthe=
y negotiated=E2=80=9D.</p><p>Another big myth is that you have to have comp=
eting offers to negotiate. You don=E2=80=99t.</p><p><span>I make a living b=
y coaching people through negotiations, and most of my earnings are result =
fees, which are dependent upon negotiating improvements in my clients=E2=80=
=99 job offers. So I have to be intentional about who I work with=E2=80=94i=
t=E2=80=99s not good for anyone if I allow people to hire me when they won=
=E2=80=99t get a good result. Yes, I get a fixed fee (a strategy fee), but =
most of my coaching revenue is from result fees.</span><br><br><span>I say =
all that to say: I don=E2=80=99t filter out potential clients based on whet=
her or not they have competing job offers for us to work with. Do they help=
? Sometimes! But not always, and they=E2=80=99re definitely not a requireme=
nt for a successful negotiation.</span></p><h3 class=3D"header-anchor-post"=
><strong>What are the 3-5 biggest </strong><em><strong>mistakes</strong></e=
m><strong> people make when negotiating their offer?</strong><div class=3D"=
pencraft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset=
 header-anchor-parent"><div class=3D"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset =
pubTheme-yiXxQA"><div class=3D"pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top" =
id=3D"=C2=A7what-are-the-biggest-mistakes-people-make-when-negotiating-thei=
r-offer"></div><button class=3D"pencraft pc-reset pencraft iconButton2-DvFP=
7w iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M buttonNew-KfJF0Q size_sm-G3LciD =
