.71"></path><path d=3D"M14 11a5 5 0 0 0-7.54-.54l-3 3a5 5 0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1=
.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div></div></h3><p>=E2=80=9CI don=E2=80=99=
t really have a number in mind right now. I=E2=80=99m excited for this oppo=
rtunity and I know I=E2=80=99ll be a valuable addition to the team. I look =
forward to hearing what you suggest in terms of comp when we get to that st=
age.=E2=80=9D</p><p>It=E2=80=99s not in your best interest to share your sa=
lary expectations. Don=E2=80=99t do it.</p><p><span>Why? Let me reframe the=
 question so it=E2=80=99s clearer what they=E2=80=99re actually asking you =
to do:</span><br><br><span>=E2=80=9CWe know you don=E2=80=99t know much abo=
ut this role=E2=80=94what our budget is, how badly we need to fill the role=
, how many other candidates we=E2=80=99re considering, the business value o=
f the role to our company, and lots of other things=E2=80=94but why don=E2=
=80=99t you take a wild guess what we=E2=80=99re willing to pay you to do t=
his job?=E2=80=9D</span></p><p>You=E2=80=99re almost certainly going to gue=
ss wrong. You=E2=80=99ll either guess low and cost yourself money, or you=
=E2=80=99ll guess too high and possibly disqualify yourself from the proces=
s.</p><p><span>Yes, it=E2=80=99s possible their offer will be too low for y=
ou to accept and that might =E2=80=9Cwaste everyone=E2=80=99s time=E2=80=9D=
, but unless you=E2=80=99re interviewing for many companies at once, the ti=
me you=E2=80=99ll spend interviewing is pretty small. And if you defer the =
compensation question as long as possible, then your performance in your in=
terviews might actually </span><em>change</em><span> their budget for the r=
ole as they realize you=E2=80=99re the perfect candidate for them.</span></=
p><p><span>If you </span><em>are</em><span> interviewing with lots of compa=
nies at once such that you really can=E2=80=99t afford to =E2=80=9Cwaste ti=
me=E2=80=9D interviewing for a role that can=E2=80=99t afford you, then the=
 issue is not solved by =E2=80=9CI should share my salary expectations with=
 these companies=E2=80=9D, but by =E2=80=9CI should be more selective about=
 the companies I=E2=80=99m interviewing with=E2=80=9D.</span></p><p><span>F=
or a </span><em>lot</em><span> more on this, here is a detailed article on =
how to handle this question, why it=E2=80=99s not in your best interest to =
share this information and a lot more:</span></p><p><a href=3D"https://fear=
lesssalarynegotiation.com/salary-expectations-interview-question/" rel=3D""=
>How to answer salary expectations questions</a></p><h3 class=3D"header-anc=
hor-post"><strong>How can I figure out my market value? Are there any data =
sources you use or how does one arrive at this?</strong><div class=3D"pencr=
aft pc-display-flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset head=
er-anchor-parent"><div class=3D"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTh=
eme-yiXxQA"><div class=3D"pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top" id=3D=
"=C2=A7how-can-i-figure-out-my-market-value-are-there-any-data-sources-you-=
use-or-how-does-one-arrive-at-this"></div><button class=3D"pencraft pc-rese=
t pencraft iconButton2-DvFP7w iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x3M butto=
nNew-KfJF0Q size_sm-G3LciD priority_secondary-S63h9o" tabindex=3D"0" type=
