0 0 0 7.07 7.07l1.71-1.71"></path></svg></button></div></div></h3><p>There =
are really two components to a counter offer: What to ask for, and how much=
 to ask for.</p><p>For the =E2=80=9Cwhat=E2=80=9D I suggest identifying the=
 top three or four things that you care about in the offer (base salary, eq=
uity, sign-on bonus, and bonus structure are usually the top ones) and rank=
ing them in terms of what is most important to you. You should almost alway=
s negotiate on one of those items at a time, so you=E2=80=99ll start with t=
he first one.</p><p>There are also some wrinkles here, like it might be bet=
ter to actually counter on =E2=80=9Ctotal comp=E2=80=9D, which will often e=
ncompass all of those items, especially for big tech-type offers.</p><p>Onc=
e you=E2=80=99ve determined what you=E2=80=99ll ask for, you have to determ=
ine =E2=80=9Chow much=E2=80=9D to ask for.</p><p>The main factor I consider=
 when deciding how much to counter is how motivated they are to hire you. I=
 often describe this as =E2=80=9CHow badly do they need you, specifically, =
to fill this role?=E2=80=9D You can call this your =E2=80=9Caggression fact=
or=E2=80=9D.</p><p>So you=E2=80=99ll calculate your aggression factor on a =
scale of 0 to 10, then add your aggression factor to 10%, giving you ao fin=
al number between 10% and 20%.</p><p>Ask for that much more of the thing yo=
u have listed first on your list of priorities.</p><p><span>Here is a </spa=
n><a href=3D"https://fearlesssalarynegotiation.com/salary-negotiation-scrip=
t/" rel=3D"">counter offer calculator</a><span> that will help you get star=
ted.</span></p><h3 class=3D"header-anchor-post"><strong>How do you think ab=
out equity during a negotiation?</strong><div class=3D"pencraft pc-display-=
flex pc-alignItems-center pc-position-absolute pc-reset header-anchor-paren=
t"><div class=3D"pencraft pc-display-contents pc-reset pubTheme-yiXxQA"><di=
v class=3D"pencraft pc-reset header-anchor offset-top" id=3D"=C2=A7how-do-y=
ou-think-about-equity-during-a-negotiation"></div><button class=3D"pencraft=
 pc-reset pencraft iconButton2-DvFP7w iconButtonBase-dJGHgN buttonBase-GK1x=
